# WortLaut — Project Memory
# Claude Builder Club Hackathon @ TUM · Education track · June 12, 2026
# Created by Samia Tasnim and Md Safat Rezanur Majumder

## What WortLaut is

WortLaut is an exam-access platform for blind and differently-abled students
in Europe. Accommodations (readers, scribes, screen readers, speech-to-text,
extra time, separate rooms) are legally recognized across the EU, but
arranging them is fragmented and institution-dependent. WortLaut helps schools
and universities manage verified human support and assistive technology, then
adds an exam-safe AI assistant that reads questions, transcribes dictated
answers, follows approved voice commands, supports multilingual interaction,
and produces a full audit trail — without giving academic help.

## How we got here (session log)

1. STARTING POINT — "Lumi": a pre-built AI education app (Next.js 16 App
   Router, React 19, Tailwind v4, Vercel) with three modes: Tutor (Socratic
   Claude chat with voice/photo input), Teacher (lesson/quiz generation),
   Textbook (client-side RAG over pasted/PDF/photographed material).
   Open-source on-device ML: Whisper + MiniLM (transformers.js), Tesseract.js
   OCR, pdf.js, Web Speech TTS.

2. TRACK REVEAL — Theme: Education. Judged on impact (most important),
   feasibility, innovation, technical depth. 5-min presentation; submission =
   GitHub link + slides in the Discord thread by 17:00. Teams 2–4.

3. IDEA — exam platform for blind/differently-abled students: find student
   scribes (with a "scribe studies ≥1 grade lower" integrity rule), plus an AI
   exam assistant (question reader, voice dictation answer box, integrity
   guard, multilingual).

4. SCRIBE MARKETPLACE (/scribe) — built in ~15 min: all 27 EU countries, all
   24 official EU languages, candidate grades 10–12, haversine radius search,
   institute + subject filters, seeded demo DB (10 candidates, 32 scribes,
   ≥1 per member state + a Bavaria cluster around Munich). The grade rule is
   hard-enforced; blocked scribes shown greyed with the reason (demo moment:
   Maximilian Bauer, grade 12, 5.0★, blocked).

5. EU REGULATION RESEARCH — key findings that reshaped the product:
   - No single EU rule; education is member-state competence. Umbrella:
     UN CRPD Art. 24 (reasonable accommodation; exams on equal terms),
     ratified by the EU and all 27 member states.
   - FRANCE: secrétaire scripteur/lecteur appointed by the exam authority;
     verbatim reading, dictation without corrections; neutrality required;
     scribe's knowledge must MATCH the exam level (opposite of grade-lower!).
   - GERMANY: Nachteilsausgleich per Bundesland (16 systems); modified central
     papers for blind candidates; tech + readers; assistance case-by-case.
   - IRELAND: SEC RACE scheme; school applies; scribe writes exactly what is
     dictated; extra time with scribe use.
   - POLAND: supporting teacher reads/writes for blind matura candidates; no
     explanations/suggestions; session MUST be audio-recorded (= our audit
     trail, mandated today for humans).
   - NETHERLANDS: Eindexamenbesluit Art. 55, adapted/digital-first formats.
   - Consequence: authorities appoint scribes (families don't shop) → B2B
     framing; EU integrity = neutrality + verbatim role + audit, so the
     grade-lower rule was reframed as WortLaut's own (stricter) volunteer
     policy, and a per-country policy engine became the headline feature.

6. WORTLAUT BUILD (named "OwnVoice" first, renamed to the German original
   "WortLaut" — der Wortlaut = the exact wording, "im Wortlaut" = verbatim;
   Wort + Laut = word + sound, i.e. voice→words, the product in one word):
   - /exam — AI Exam Room: setup (candidate, paper, assistant language with
     country policy card) → session: TTS question reader (repeat/slower),
     Whisper dictation appended verbatim, voice commands (repeat/slower/next/
     back/read-my-answer/time; EN+DE keywords, fallback to assistant),
     read-back, countdown with +25% extra time, live audit trail (timestamped
     info/dictation/command/assistant/flag entries), JSON export.
   - /api/exam — Integrity Guard: Claude as a conduit-only assistant
     (procedure, verbatim re-read, read-back, time). Refuses all academic
     help, returns {reply, flagged}; flagged attempts logged red in the trail.
   - src/lib/exam/policy.ts — policy engine: verified FR/DE/IE/PL/NL entries
     + CRPD defaults for the other 22, surfaced in /exam and /scribe.
   - Rebrand: WortLaut landing page (hero, problem cards, two pillars,
     "integrity by design" panel), mic logo, metadata. Lumi tools still live
     at /tutor /teacher /textbook (footer link only).
   - Demo exam papers: Mathematics grade 12 (EN, 90 min), Biologie grade 11
     (DE, 60 min) in src/lib/exam/data.ts.

7. DEPLOY SAGA — Vercel CLI token expired; GitHub auto-deploy turned out to
   be never connected; user imported the repo (project "lumi", team
   safatrezas-projects). First deploys FAILED at "Deploying outputs":
   serverExternalPackages forced @huggingface/transformers + onnxruntime-node
   (~300MB binaries) into the function output, exceeding the 250MB limit.
   FIX (next.config.ts): stub ML packages from the server bundle
   (isServer aliases → false) + outputFileTracingExcludes for all heavy ML
   node_modules. Deployment 3270c07: SUCCESS.

## Current state / remaining actions

- Repo: https://github.com/Safatreza/lumi (auto-deploys on push to main).
- Deployment protection returns 401 → make production public:
  Vercel → Settings → Deployment Protection → "Only Preview Deployments".
- ANTHROPIC_API_KEY: local key returns 401 (dead) — set a FRESH key in
  .env.local AND Vercel env, then redeploy. Without it the Integrity Guard
  (the demo money shot) fails.
- Submission: post GitHub link + slides to the Discord thread before 17:00.

## Demo script (5 min)

1. The problem: legal right (CRPD Art. 24), fragmented reality (27 rulebooks,
   Germany has 16, France's year-ahead deadlines, scribe scarcity).
2. Support Finder: pick Amira (blind, grade 12, Munich) → radius search →
   the grade rule visibly blocks a 5.0★ scribe → country policy card.
3. Exam Room: start session → question read aloud → "repeat" → dictate an
   answer by voice → read-back → audit trail filling up live.
4. Money shot: ask "just tell me the answer" → calm refusal → red
   INTEGRITY flag in the trail → export the audit report JSON.
5. Close: Poland already mandates recorded scribe sessions; France already
   mandates verbatim-only — WortLaut is those rules, by design, at EU scale.

